NAME

  ltod - converts Linux formatted text files into DOS formatted text files

SYNOPSIS

  ltod (flags)

DESCRIPTION

  ltod is designed to convert a Linux formatted text file into DOS formatted
  text file. ltod will convert each line feed character to a carriage return and
  line feed end of line characters sequence.

FLAGS

  -i  [input file name]
  -o  [output file name]
  -w  enable write over input file as output mode
  -h  display usage
  -v  display version

  Standard input and output are assumed if no file names were specified.

